         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>132</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... was released. There was a sea monster in the ocean ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1968"/><citedRange>210</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... in Śrāvasti the masters of the guilds (met?). Śrivṛddhi was [there]. ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>88</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... because of ... do not rejoice in birth! ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... belonging to blood. You (sg.) should go! ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>403</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... going towards ... in rebirths. 2. Like the Udumbara flower ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1983"/><citedRange>38</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... go (pl.) out of the house! Adopt the homelessness! ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... gehet [und] übet die Hauslosigkeit!</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... go [ye] and practice houselessness!</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>350</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... If you (pl.) are freed from sorrow, you will obtain ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... they got a (gre)at disgust towards the great pleasures ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... being disgusted, freeing (other beings?) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... high like a pole ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... having done ... he says: (In) [the tune] pañcagati: ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>230</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... Which blood I separated from the body ... </seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">Left part of a leaf with the string hole space covering lines 3 and 4. The leaf number on the left margin is 27, but inside the string hole space on the verso side we find the number 26; note that this manuscript often shows deviating numbering inside the string hole.</note><note corresp="#b5" type="philcomment">The tune pañcagati has the meter 21|21|18|13 (ab: 8/7/6, c: 9/9, d: 7/6).</note></p>
